[13.323016, "o", "Error: Governance error: Oversimplified code detected: \"fn validate_user_input(input) {\r\n    return true\r\n}\" [HARD-MANDATORY]\r\n\r\n  At: line 2\r\n  Rule (govern.json): code_quality.no_oversimplification\r\n\r\n  Help:\r\n  - This code is a stub, placeholder, or trivially incomplete.\r\n  - The most common fix: DELETE the qualifying comment.\r\n  - If the code underneath works, the comment was the only problem.\r\n  - Comments should explain WHY, not admit the code is incomplete.\r\n  - \r\n  -   Do NOT add hedging comments like:\r\n  -     \"for now\", \"simplified\", \"basic implementation\",\r\n  -     \"in a real system\", \"would normally\", \"for demonstration\"\r\n\r\n  Example:\r\n    ✗ Blocked:\r\n      // basic implementation for now\r\n      fn process(data) {\r\n          return data  // would normally transform\r\n      }\r\n    ✓ Allowed:\r\n      fn process(data) {\r\n          let result = []\r\n          for item in data {\r\n              let transformed = apply_rules(item)\r\n              result.push(transformed)\r\n          }\r\n          return result\r\n      }\r\n\r\n"]
