[21.503991, "o", "[governance] Loaded: /data/data/com.termux/files/home/.naab/language/demo/govern.json (mode: enforce)\r\n"]
[21.507662, "o", "Error: Governance error: Incomplete logic detected: \"catch (e) {\r\n    }\" [HARD-MANDATORY]\r\n\r\n  At: line 2\r\n  Rule (govern.json): code_quality.no_incomplete_logic\r\n\r\n  Help:\r\n  - This code has logic gaps — shortcuts or lazy implementation.\r\n  - Every function should DO something meaningful:\r\n  -   - Error handlers must log or re-raise, never silently swallow\r\n  -   - Return values must be computed, not hardcoded\r\n  -   - Loops must process data, not immediately break\r\n  - \r\n  -   NAAb-specific fixes:\r\n  -   - catch (e) { } → catch (e) { print(\"Error: \" + string(e)); throw e }\r\n  -   - fn validate(x) { return true } → add real checks\r\n  -   - score = 0.85 → score = len(matches) / len(total)\r\n\r\n  Example:\r\n    ✗ Blocked:\r\n      catch (e) { }  // empty catch swallows error\r\n      fn validate(x) { return true }  // always passes\r\n      let score = 0.85  // hardcoded\r\n    ✓ Allowed:\r\n      catch (e) { print(\"Error: \" + string(e)); throw e }\r\n      fn validate(x) {\r\n          if x == null { return false }\r\n          if len(x) == 0 { return false }\r\n          return true\r\n      }\r\n      let score = len(matches) / len(total)\r\n\r\n"]
[21.515289, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;31m\u001b[1m  ✗ Blocked by governance\u001b[0m\r\n"]
